### TransformRecommendations Demo - HTTP Requests
### Send these through the proxymock inbound proxy on port 4143
### Compatible with VS Code REST Client and JetBrains HTTP Client

@host = http://localhost:3000

### Health check
GET {{host}}/

### DATETIME: outbound request with timestamp in body
POST {{host}}/api/report
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reportName": "weekly-sync"
}

### JWT_RESIGN / OAUTH: Basic auth handshake that returns access_token
### Credentials: demo-client / demo-secret (any username:password is accepted by the demo)
# @name authToken
POST {{host}}/api/auth/token
Authorization: Basic ZGVtby1jbGllbnQ6ZGVtby1zZWNyZXQ=

### JWT propagation: subsequent Bearer call -> /api/auth/validate (outbound with Authorization)
POST {{host}}/api/data
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken.response.body.access_token}}

{
  "action": "resolve-roles"
}

### REQUEST_ID (inbound + outbound): call with X-Request-Id header
POST {{host}}/api/search
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-Id: my-test-request-id-001

{
  "query": "sample"
}

### DLP: outbound call with email, phone, credit card, SSN in body
POST {{host}}/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### DLP (response): authenticated profile lookup returns sensitive data
### Run the "Basic auth handshake" request above first (Bearer from that response)
GET {{host}}/api/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken.response.body.access_token}}

### DATETIME + REQUEST_ID combined: timestamp in body + X-Request-Id header
POST {{host}}/api/events
Content-Type: application/json
X-Request-Id: events-trace-id-002

{}
